One who is not a
dweller within some jurisdiction in question ;
not an inhabitant of the state of the forum.
Gardner v. Meeker, 169 Ill. 40, 48 N. E. 307;
Nagel v. Loomis, 33 Neb. 499, 50 N. W. 441;
Morgan v. Nunes, 54 Miss. 310. For the
distinction between “residence” and “domicile,” see DOMICILE.
